message.content: cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.LG. The paper deals with conversational systems and information retrieval, which are relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses user satisfaction and frustration, which are related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper proposes a retrieval framework and evaluates it using machine learning techniques, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
